SWISS NATIONAL BANK REJECTS BITCOIN BACKING

The Swiss National Bank has dismissed Bitcoin as a reserve asset—citing volatility, liquidity constraints, and security risks. 

President Martin Schlegel argues that BTC doesn’t meet the stability required for central bank reserves and questions its relevance in global finance.

Meanwhile, a grassroots initiative is working to force the issue onto a national vote.

Even in Switzerland, Bitcoin’s path to institutional adoption faces an uphill climb.

Source: Bitcoin.comNews
